Global Funds Buy Net 16.8 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-07-01T03:31:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/global-funds-buy-net-16-8-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 16.8
billion rupees ($377 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 40 percent to 674 billion rupees, or 36.8
percent of the gross market position on the last day of trading
for contracts of June, according to the exchangeâ€™s website. Open
interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 15.9 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
